lead_paragraph: Reggie Jackson scored 24 points and Kentavious Caldwell-Pope added 18 to help lead the Detroit Pistons to a 108-104 win over the Orlando Magic on Wednesday night.

headline.print_headline: Pistons Use Strong Second Half to Get Past Magic 108-104
